# Telemetry ingest & historian (prod reference)

**Prod:** `ispf.iot-solutions.ru` · **0.9.100** (июль 2026).

## MQTT gateway (`mqtt-gateway-v1`, fixture)

Fixture RELATIVE-модель (`ispf.bootstrap.fixtures-enabled`). См. [docs/en/decisions/0018-fixture-models-and-cel-applicability.md](../../docs/en/decisions/0018-fixture-models-and-cel-applicability.md).

- One MQTT connection; `ingressVariable=lastIngress`, `ingressTopicLanes=true`
- Hot path: `MqttGatewayIngressDispatchService` → `dispatchTelemetry` → child `temperature.value`
- Loadtest: `deploy/mqtt-ingress-load-test.py --gateway`

## Historian write

- `ispf.variable-history.store=jdbc` (default) — `JdbcVariableHistoryWriteStore`, not JPA `saveAll`
- Env: `ISPF_VARIABLE_HISTORY_MIN_INTERVAL_MS=1` for loadtest only (default 5000)
- `ISPF_DB_URL=...?reWriteBatchedInserts=true`

## Binding periodic rules

- `activators.periodicMs > 0` → JDBC index `platform_binding_periodic_rules`
- `BindingPeriodicScheduler` — один wake на ближайший `next_run_at`, без секундного обхода дерева
- См. [docs/en/bindings.md](../../docs/en/bindings.md)

## Thread pools (do not multiply blindly)

| Config | Default | Notes |
|--------|---------|-------|
| `ispf.binding.async-threads` | 16 | Not on gateway hot path when `ingressTopicLanes=true` |
| `ispf.mqtt-gateway.ingress-dispatch-threads` | 8 | Gateway dispatch |
| `ispf.variable-history.writer-threads` | 4 | JDBC batch writer |
| `ispf.runtime-telemetry.coalesce-scheduler-threads` | 4 | Coalesce timers |

## Load diagnostics & metrics probe

- UI: Admin → System → Metrics → **Load diagnostics** (`DiagnosticsPressureCard`)
- Cluster fan-out: `GET /api/v1/platform/cluster/diagnostics`
- Metrics probe (runtime only): `PUT /api/v1/platform/diagnostics/metrics-probe` → `root.platform.devices.platform-metrics-probe`
- Boot env `ISPF_PLATFORM_METRICS_PROBE_ENABLED` **не** стартует scheduler — только UI/API toggle
- См. [docs/en/observability.md](../../docs/en/observability.md), [docs/en/cluster.md](../../docs/en/cluster.md)

## Baselines (gateway, 4 devices, ~2k msg/s)

